collections.name: CollectionUrbanArt 2025
collections.description: This captivating painting wonderfully expresses the raw and chaotic energy of Urban Life. The juxtaposition of graphic elements, black-and-white patterns, and touches of newspaper collages creates a vibrant and emotionally charged atmosphere. The central figures, blending skeletons and expressive faces, embody a duality between life and death, light and shadow, within an urban setting where visual anarchy reflects the complexity of the city. The rich details—symbols, graffiti, and fragmented architecture—tell a story, one of a city fueled by its vibrancy and contrasts. A powerful piece that captures the soul of modern urban life with a unique and assertive style.

collections.name: FRAGMENTS of INFINITY
collections.description: “Fragments of Infinity” is a captivating compositional system that delves into the boundless possibilities of abstract forms and colors, creating an immersive visual experience that evokes the essence of infinity. Central to this exploration is the dynamic interplay of light and shadow, which not only adds depth and dimension but also simulates various atmospheric conditions, enhancing the perception of an expansive, limitless space. Each fragment within the composition possesses unique characteristics influenced by parameters such as light intensity and color saturation, allowing for a rich tapestry of variability that mirrors organic growth. The fluid relationship between the fragments and their background blurs the boundaries of figure and ground, fostering a harmonious dialogue that emphasizes unity within diversity. collections.name: NN-F-1 Collection N.N. to ashes
collections.description:
One of a series of oil paintings i painted a few years ago and entitled „nude nature“ is the basis of this NFT.

I had the idea of ​​"reduced to the maximum" and put the oil painting under fire and took 13 photos of the burning process.

These NFTs are pictures taken of the burning performance. The NFTs represents a digital photograph of an original oil painting. Purchase of the NFTs does not imply any transfer of copyright or ownership of the physical painting.

I saved the ashes from this process so that I could later make an ink from it. I will use this ink to create a brush stroke and that is how we came up with the idea of ​​reducing to the max.

Please stay tuned until I paint these brush strokes and create a new collection with the title „reducing to the max“

collections.name: Waves of Creation
collections.description:
Dive into the intricate dance of waveforms in "Waves of Creation," a digital art collection that celebrates the sine wave as a universal symbol of life and energy. In both the cosmos and the human body, waveforms are at the core of creation, shaping everything from the rhythms of the universe to the vibrations within us.
Each piece in this collection is a unique digital artwork, meticulously crafted by István using his imagination, mathematical and physical equations, numerical sequences, and the pervasive beauty of randomness. The sine wave takes center stage, representing the unifying force that connects the macro and micro worlds, while vibrant designs, inspired by the interplay of order and chaos, create a symphony of color and form.
Inspired by the rhythms of the universe and the inner workings of the human body, these one-of-a-kind digital artworks invite viewers to delve into a mesmerizing interplay of order and chaos.

collections.name: LEVEL 1
collections.description: "LEVEL 1" is a collection of photographs shot on Cinestill 800T film, capturing the stark beauty of urban underworlds. These images explore the hidden spaces beneath the city, from dimly lit parking garages and abandoned tunnels to forgotten basements and subterranean passageways. The use of Cinestill 800T film lends a unique cinematic quality to the images, with its signature grain and muted colors creating a dreamlike and atmospheric feel. Each photograph in this collection invites the viewer to delve into the depths of the urban landscape and discover the hidden beauty that lies beneath the surface.

collections.name: Freedom Street Vybz Kartel
collections.description:
Step into history with the "Freedom Street" NFT – a one-of-a-kind digital masterpiece commemorating Vybz Kartel's triumphant return to the stage after 13 years. This vibrant cartoon-style artwork captures the electrifying energy of his first live appearance, showcasing the legendary dancehall artist standing tall on the iconic "Freedom Street."

Every detail of this piece tells a story – from the bold graffiti emblazoned with his name, to the colorful Jamaican street vibes and his signature style complete with tattoos, gold chains, and unmistakable charisma. Owning this NFT is more than just acquiring art; it's becoming a part of dancehall history.

Whether you're a die-hard Kartel fan or a collector of cultural milestones, "Freedom Street" is a must-have addition to your collection. Be part of this monumental moment and celebrate the legacy of the Worl' Boss in style!

🔥 Limited Edition – Own a Piece of Dancehall History! 🔥

This collection challenges the viewer to think deeply about the very nature of humanity by placing them in modern day settings.

collections.name: QUEEN & QUEEN
collections.description:
QUEEN & QUEEN series explores an enduring symbol of female power - the queen. Throughout history, queens have embodied far more than mere hereditary authority; they represent the pinnacle of feminine influence, wisdom, and commanding presence. While historical narratives often spotlight kings, visionary queens like Cleopatra VII and Elizabeth I proved that women could be transformative forces, fundamentally reshaping societies and civilizations through their leadership.
Artist boldly reimagines queenship for the 21st century. Her queens derive their authority not from royal lineage but from their own fierce authenticity, determination, and achievements. The pieces interweave portraits of historical monarchs with images of modern female pioneers - innovative executives, groundbreaking scientists, visionary artists, and community leaders.
